definitions.definition: To jump , fall , descend , etc. using such a device.
To introduce into a place using such a device.
examples: The soldiers were parachuted behind enemy lines.

definitions.definition: To place (somebody) in an organisation in a position of authority without their having previous experience there; used with in or into .
To wrap illicit drugs in a covering before swallowing them, so that they will be released for absorption when the covering dissolves within the body.

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To jump , fall , descend , etc. using such a device.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To introduce into a place using such a device.
( transitive ) To place (somebody) in an organisation in a position of authority without their having previous experience there; used with in or into .
( slang ) To wrap illicit drugs in a covering before swallowing them, so that they will be released for absorption when the covering dissolves within the body.
